    "Table 4 DRAGON-AI results for relationship prediction taskWe partition into two subtasks: filtered for SubClassOf, and filtered for all relationship types (heterogeneous relationship predictions).",
    "We also show OWL DL Reasoning results for the SubClassOf task.",
    "Note that by definition OWL DL reasoning is always completely precise as all entailments follow from existing axiomsSubClassOf Task All Relationship Types Task method model precision recall F1 precision recall F1 DRAGON gpt-3.5-turbo 0.846 0.419 0.561 0.758 0.446 0.562 DRAGON gpt-4 0.894 0.5 0.642 0.802 0.505 0.62 DRAGON nous-hermes-13b 0.73 0.353 0.476 0.64 0.355 0.457 Reasoner n/a 1.0* 0.337 0.504 n/a n/a n/a DRAGON-AI can read and interpret GitHub issues to improve performanceWe investigated whether providing background knowledge from GitHub issue trackers would improve the quality of generated definitions.",
    "All of the evaluated ontologies are in the OBO Foundry, and all have their own issue tracker.",
    "These trackers are used by the broader community (domain experts, curators, users of the ontology) to file issues requesting changes to the ontology or new terms."
